<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1823] XMLWriter throws ClassCastException on writing maps other than &lt;String,?&gt;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1823</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/api/org/apache/solr/response/SolrQueryResponse.html#returnable_data&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://lucene.apache.org/solr/api/org/apache/solr/response/SolrQueryResponse.html#returnable_data&lt;/a&gt; says that a Map &quot;containing any of the items in this list&quot; may be contained in a SolrQueryResponse and will be handled by QueryResponseWriters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is not true for (at least) Keys in Maps.&lt;br/&gt;
XMLWriter tries to cast keys to Strings. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12459137">SOLR-1823</key>
            <summary>XMLWriter throws ClassCastException on writing maps other than &lt;String,?&gt;</summary>
